'''Gordon "Gordie" Douglas Roberts''' (Born [[October 2]], [[1957]] in [[Detroit, Michigan]]) was an [[National Hockey League|NHL]] defenseman from 1979 to 1994 and spent most of his time with the [[Minnesota North Stars]]. He was drafted in the third round, 54th overall by the [[Montreal Canadiens]] in the [[1977 NHL Amateur Draft]]. Roberts was also the assistant coach of the [[Phoenix Coyotes]] for the 1998 and 1999 seasons. He won 2 [[Stanley Cup]]s with the [[Pittsburgh Penguins]] in [[1990-91 NHL season|1991]] and [[1991-92 NHL season|1992]].

